# Testing

## Layers
- Unit: money value object, FX conversion + rounding, version-gate logic, idempotency decision.
  Pure, fast, no I/O.
- Integration: real Postgres via Testcontainers (`@testcontainers/postgresql`). Run actual migrations.
- Kafka flow: Testcontainers Kafka (or a fake consumer harness) for delta + snapshot + duplicate + stale.

## Mandatory tests (do not mark a feature done without these)
1. CONCURRENCY: fire N parallel reservations that together exceed the limit; assert total reserved
   never exceeds `total_limit` and exactly the right number succeed. This proves the atomic invariant.
2. IDEMPOTENCY: submit the same reservation twice (same key) -> exactly one ledger row, one effect.
3. STALE SNAPSHOT: apply version 5, then deliver version 3 -> ignored, state unchanged.
4. OUT-OF-ORDER: snapshot v10 after delta v8 applied -> snapshot wins; delta v8 replayed after -> ignored.
5. CURRENCY MISMATCH: reserve in a currency differing from program base -> either converts with a
   persisted rate, or rejects — matching the documented decision. Assert no silent mixed-currency sum.
6. RELEASE: reserve then release -> available returns to original; double-release is idempotent/rejected.

## Style
- Arrange/Act/Assert, one behaviour per test, descriptive names.
- No sleeps for concurrency — use `Promise.all` / barriers. Deterministic assertions only.
- Money assertions on integer minor units, never on formatted strings.
